Canada's Erik Guay Wins Men's Downhill at World Skiing Championships

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-02-12T12:28:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-12/canada-s-erik-guay-wins-men-s-downhill-at-world-skiing-championships.html
Erik Guay won the men’s downhill at
the Alpine World Championships to become the second consecutive
Canadian to capture the title.  Guay, 29, had a winning time of 1 minute, 58.41 seconds on
the Kandahar course in Garmish-Partenkirchen,  Germany . He
succeeds countryman John Kucera, who won two years ago, as world
downhill champion.    Switzerland ’s Didier Cuche, the current  World Cup  downhill
leader, was 0.32 seconds behind in second place. Italy’s
Christof Innerhofer, who won the super-G three days ago,
finished third, 0.76 seconds back.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  